Linux Vim Editor – Practice Task
Task Objective

As part of my Linux learning for DevOps, I practiced using the Vim editor.
Vim is a powerful text editor widely used in Linux servers to create and edit configuration files.

The objective of this task was to understand how to create, edit, save, and manage files using Vim.

Task Scenario

Assume I am working on a Linux server and I need to create a configuration file for a DevOps project.

In this task, I practiced:

Creating a new file using Vim
Writing text inside the file
Editing the content
Deleting lines
Copying and pasting text
Saving and exiting the file



Commands Practiced

vim filename
i
!
dd
yy
p

Learning Outcome

From this practice task, I learned:

How to open and create files using Vim
The difference between command mode and insert mode
How to add and edit text in Vim
How to save and exit files
How to delete, copy, and paste lines

This practice helped me understand how developers and DevOps engineers edit configuration files directly on Linux servers using Vim.
